NO. The proposed patch attempts to fix the bug by adding a special case for patterns of length one, simply checking if the pattern is in the text, but this does not address the fundamental issue with the rolling hash update formula. The core problem is that the rolling hash calculation incorrectly updates the hash by subtracting the ordinal of the outgoing character without accounting for its positional weight (modulus_power), which causes the hash to diverge from the intended polynomial form after the first window shift. The patch does not modify this critical part of the algorithm, so the hash mismatch and missed matches for patterns occurring after the first window remain unresolved. Therefore, the patch is insufficient and does not correctly fix the bug described.
